Classification.Comment: The c.3281dupT pathogenic mutation, located in coding exon 29 of the ANK2 gene, results from a duplication of T at nucleotide position 3281, causing a translational frameshift with a predicted alternate stop codon (p.V1095Gfs*6). This variant is considered to be rare based on population cohorts in the Genome Aggregation Database (gnomAD). This alteration is expected to result in loss of function by premature protein truncation or nonsense-mediated mRNA decay. Based on the supporting evidence, this variant is expected to be causative of ANK2-related neurodevelopmental disorder. However, the evidence for the gene-disease relationship is limited for cardiac disease; therefore, the clinical significance of this alteration for ANK2-related arrhythmia is unclear.
